title: Spectrum-X Plugin (RCP) for BCM - Unconfigured
ztp:
#!/bin/bash
#
# ZTP Script
function error() {
  echo -e "\e[0;33mERROR: Provisioning error running $BASH_COMMAND at line $BASH_LINENO of $(basename $0) \e[0m" >&2
}

function json() {
  cat "$1" | python -c "import json, sys; print(json.load(sys.stdin).get('$2', $3))"
}

# Log all output from this script
exec >/var/log/autoprovision 2>&1

trap error ERR

SSH_URL="http://192.168.200.1/authorized_keys"
# Uncomment to setup SSH key authentication for Ansible
mkdir -p /home/cumulus/.ssh
wget -qO /home/cumulus/.ssh/authorized_keys $SSH_URL

echo "changing password"
nv set system aaa user cumulus password 'Cumu1usLinux!'
nv set service ntp mgmt server 4.cumulusnetworks.pool.ntp.org iburst on

MAC_ADDR=$(cat /sys/class/net/eth0/address)
spine_s00=44:38:39:22:aa:48
spine_s01=44:38:39:22:aa:49
spine_s02=44:38:39:22:aa:4a
spine_s03=44:38:39:22:aa:4b
leaf_su00_r0=44:38:39:22:aa:40
leaf_su00_r1=44:38:39:22:aa:41
leaf_su00_r2=44:38:39:22:aa:42
leaf_su00_r3=44:38:39:22:aa:43
leaf_su01_r0=44:38:39:22:aa:44
leaf_su01_r1=44:38:39:22:aa:45
leaf_su01_r2=44:38:39:22:aa:46
leaf_su01_r3=44:38:39:22:aa:47
if [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$spine_s00" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname spine-s00
    echo "spine-s00"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$spine_s01" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname spine-s01
    echo "spine-s01"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$spine_s02" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname spine-s02
    echo "spine-s02"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$spine_s03" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname spine-s03
    echo "spine-s03"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su00_r0" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su00-r0
    echo "leaf-su00-r0"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su00_r1" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su00-r1
    echo "leaf-su00-r1"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su00_r2" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su00-r2
    echo "leaf-su00-r2"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su00_r3" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su00-r3
    echo "leaf-su00-r3"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su01_r0" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su01-r0
    echo "leaf-su01-r0"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su01_r1" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su01-r1
    echo "leaf-su01-r1"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su01_r2" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su01-r2
    echo "leaf-su01-r2"
elif [[ "$MAC_ADDR" = "$leaf_su01_r3" ]]; then
    nv set system hostname leaf-su01-r3
    echo "leaf-su01-r3"
fi

nv config apply -y

# Uncomment to make user cumulus passwordless sudo
echo "cumulus ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL" > /etc/sudoers.d/10_cumulus

# Uncomment to enable all debian sources & netq apps3 repo
#sed -i 's/#deb/deb/g' /etc/apt/sources.list
#wget -qO pubkey https://apps3.cumulusnetworks.com/setup/cumulus-apps-deb.pubkey
#apt-key add pubkey
#rm pubkey

# Pre-login banner
cat <<EOT > /etc/issue
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
   Welcome to 

   Login with: cumulus/Cumu1usLinux!
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

EOT
cp /etc/issue /etc/issue.net
chmod 755 /etc/issue /etc/issue.net

# exclude /etc/hosts from nvue
#nv set system config apply ignore /etc/hosts
#nv config apply -y      


# CUMULUS-AUTOPROVISIONING
